A group, House to House Nigeria, has said it has commenced mobilisation of members to ensure victory for the Minister of Transportation, Rotimi Amaechi to contest for the seat of the President come 2023. This was disclosed in a joint press statement issued on Wednesday at the group’s secretariat in Abuja, and signed by its National Coordinator, Alhaji Ahmed Madigawa; national spokesperson, Mr Confidence Eke; and the Board Chairman, Mr Samuel Iduh. The group pointed at several Amaechi’s achievements as the former governor of Rivers State as reasons for their confidence in him. The statement read, “As a group, we have commenced a nationwide mobilisation of members to ensure victory for the candidacy of Rt. Hon Chibuike Rotimi Amaechi who is detribalised and development oriented. “Amaechi’s scorecard in the areas of education, agriculture, healthcare, transport, roads and human capital development as executive governor of Rivers State and the present revolution in the rail and maritime subsectors of the Nigerian economy is excellent.” Copyright PUNCH All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com